f\f[B]:\f[R]
  a\f[B]:\f[R] cat
  cat\f[B]:\f[R] b
.EE
.SS Dereference and update a field
Use explode with multiply to dereference an object
.PP
Given a sample.yml file of:
.IP
.EX
item_value\f[B]:\f[R] &item_value
  value\f[B]:\f[R] true
thingOne\f[B]:\f[R]
  name\f[B]:\f[R] item_1
  !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R] *item_value
thingTwo\f[B]:\f[R]
  name\f[B]:\f[R] item_2
  !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R] *item_value
.EE
.PP
then
.IP
.EX
yq \(aq.thingOne |= (explode(.) | sort_keys(.)) * {\(dqvalue\(dq: false}\(aq sample.yml
.EE
.PP
will output
.IP
.EX
item_value\f[B]:\f[R] &item_value
  value\f[B]:\f[R] true
thingOne\f[B]:\f[R]
  name\f[B]:\f[R] item_1
  value\f[B]:\f[R] false
thingTwo\f[B]:\f[R]
  name\f[B]:\f[R] item_2
  !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R] *item_value
.EE
.SS LEGACY: Explode with merge anchors
Caution: this is for when \(enyaml\-fix\-merge\-anchor\-to\-spec=false;
it\(cqs not to YAML spec because the merge anchors incorrectly override
the object values (foobarList.b is set to bar_b when it should still be
foobarList_b).
Flag will default to true in late 2025
.PP
Given a sample.yml file of:
.IP
.EX
foo\f[B]:\f[R] &foo
  a\f[B]:\f[R] foo_a
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] foo_thing
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foo_c
bar\f[B]:\f[R] &bar
  b\f[B]:\f[R] bar_b
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] bar_thing
  c\f[B]:\f[R] bar_c
foobarList\f[B]:\f[R]
  b\f[B]:\f[R] foobarList_b
  !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R]
    \f[B]\-\f[R] *foo
    \f[B]\-\f[R] *bar
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foobarList_c
foobar\f[B]:\f[R]
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foobar_c
  !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R] *foo
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] foobar_thing
.EE
.PP
then
.IP
.EX
yq \(aqexplode(.)\(aq sample.yml
.EE
.PP
will output
.IP
.EX
foo\f[B]:\f[R]
  a\f[B]:\f[R] foo_a
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] foo_thing
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foo_c
bar\f[B]:\f[R]
  b\f[B]:\f[R] bar_b
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] bar_thing
  c\f[B]:\f[R] bar_c
foobarList\f[B]:\f[R]
  b\f[B]:\f[R] bar_b
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] foo_thing
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foobarList_c
  a\f[B]:\f[R] foo_a
foobar\f[B]:\f[R]
  c\f[B]:\f[R] foo_c
  a\f[B]:\f[R] foo_a
  thing\f[B]:\f[R] foobar_thing
.EE
.SS LEGACY: Merge multiple maps
see https://yaml.org/type/merge.html.
This has the correct data, but the wrong key order; set
\(enyaml\-fix\-merge\-anchor\-to\-spec=true to fix the key order.
.PP
Given a sample.yml file of:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]\-\f[R] &CENTRE
  x\f[B]:\f[R] 1
  y\f[B]:\f[R] 2
\f[B]\-\f[R] &LEFT
  x\f[B]:\f[R] 0
  y\f[B]:\f[R] 2
\f[B]\-\f[R] &BIG
  r\f[B]:\f[R] 10
\f[B]\-\f[R] &SMALL
  r\f[B]:\f[R] 1
\f[B]\-\f[R] !!merge <<\f[B]:\f[R]
    \f[B]\-\f[R] *CENTRE
    \f[B]\-\f[R] *BIG
.EE
.PP
then
.IP
.EX
yq \(aq.[4] | explode(.)\(aq sample.yml
.EE
.PP
will output
.IP
.EX
r\f[B]:\f[R] 10
x\f[B]:\f[R] 1
y\f[B]:\f[R] 2
